COZY!  This is the pub you wish you were at! It's an old pub through and through.  Decor is perfect; bricks are exposed, ducts are exposed and painted black, and iron chandeliers hang from the ceiling.  On this slow-after-Christmas-day cat videos play in an endless loop on the far TV and 'Night at the Roxbury' silent plays on another other screen with closed captioning.  All-the-while Lo-fi techno pushes forward drowning out the conversations of regulars, and the distant ringing of a phone.  I recommend hooking a left on your way in and dining in the basement.  Located in Judicary Square, and the theme does not disappoint.  Legal-ese covers the walls!  You'll find yourself surrounded by slogans like "Any road will get you there if you dont know where you are going" and "In case of indictment break glass."  -Staff is friendly. -Happy hour specials are excellent. -Fish and chips is outstanding (mini portion is avaliable if you are scheduled for dinner elsewhere) -Not far from courts, law school, Union Station, the capitol, and/or the Department of Labor.  ❤ this review? The food was excellent.  I had the mini Wellington appy which was really good.  My wife had the vegetarian bangers and mashed, also outstanding.  In my experience vegetable-based sausages usually taste weird and unfamiliar however The Alibi's version were delicious.  To balance the good food, our service was absolutely horrible.  I told our server that I wanted to start with the mini Wellington and see about a main course after.  He left me a menu for when he returned, however he didn't return for almost a half hour.  He spent most of this time joking around and chit-chatting behind the bar instead of taking care of customers.  The server also never offered water- we finally had to ask at the very end, which is when he noticed he had left me a menu to order a main course.  Was a little late at this point to ask me about ordering and I told him "that ship has sailed."  When he brought the check, he apologized that it was a "miscommunication."  Which part was a communication- leaving the menu so I could select a main course a few minutes later??  Or was joking around and fiddling behind the bar communication that somehow I didn't understand???  Ugh.  Strictly amateur.  I recommend the self-service here.

Rotisserie chicken is to die for plus good cold beer. Will highly recommend this place to anyone who askes and when we come back to D.C., we will be coming back

I ended up with a glass of what looked like dirty dish water that I felt was entirely unpleasant. Maybe a tea drinker could appreciate it, but not me.

My husband and I met one of our friends at The Alibi for lunch. We were pleasantly surprised at the quaint ambiance and decor. Our server/bartender, Alisha (she was doing double duty on the second floor) was very informative. She described to us several of the beers they served and helped with a selection. My husband had fish and chips that were crispy and delicious. Our friend had a salmon dish that was cooked perfectly and I had a Caesar salad that was enough for 2 people. Alisha was very friendly, efficient, and a great bartender. I highly recommend The Alibi and if you decide to eat there ask for Alisha. You will not be disappointed.
